House Bill 843
By: Representatives Carpenter of the 4th, Ridley of the 6th, and Tarvin of the 2nd
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act to provide for a homestead exemption from City of Dalton ad valorem
2 taxes for municipal purposes in the amount of $150,000.00 of the assessed value of the
3 homestead for residents of that city who are 70 years of age or over, approved May 17, 2004
4 (Ga. L. 2004, p. 3766), as amended, so as to increase such exemption; to revise provisions
5 for the grandfathering of certain residents; to provide for compliance with constitutional
6 requirements; to provide for a referendum, effective dates, automatic repeal, mandatory
7 execution of election, and judicial remedies regarding failure to comply; to provide for
8 related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 An Act to provide for a homestead exemption from City of Dalton ad valorem taxes for
12 municipal purposes in the amount of $150,000.00 of the assessed value of the homestead for
13 residents of that city who are 70 years of age or over, approved May 17, 2004 (Ga. L. 2004,
14 p. 3766), as amended, is amended by revising subsection (b) of Section 1 as follows:
15 "(b) Each resident of the City of Dalton who is a senior citizen is granted an exemption on
16 that person's homestead from City of Dalton ad valorem taxes for municipal purposes in
