17 the amount of $325,000.00 of the assessed value of that homestead. The value of that
18 property in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation."
19 SECTION 2.
20 In accordance with the requirements of Article VII, Section II of the Constitution of the State
21 of Georgia, this Act shall not become law unless it receives the requisite two-thirds' majority
22 vote in both the Senate and the House of Representatives.
23 SECTION 3.
24 The municipal election superintendent of the City of Dalton shall call and conduct an election
25 as provided in this section for the purpose of submitting this Act to the electors of the City
26 of Dalton for approval or rejection. The municipal election superintendent shall conduct that
27 election on any permissible special election date under Code Section 21-2-540 of the
28 O.C.G.A., but not later than the November, 2026, general election and shall issue the call and
29 conduct such election as provided by general law. The municipal election superintendent
30 shall cause the date and purpose of the election to be published once a week for two weeks
31 immediately preceding the date thereof in the official organ of Whitfield County. The ballot
32 shall have written or printed thereon the words:
33 "( ) YES Shall the Act be approved which increases the homestead exemption from
34 ( ) NO City of Dalton ad valorem taxes for municipal purposes for citizens age 70
35 years or over to the amount of $325,000.00 of the assessed value of the
36 homestead?"
37 All persons desiring to vote for approval of the Act shall vote "Yes," and all persons desiring
38 to vote for rejection of the Act shall vote "No." If more than one-half of the votes cast on
39 such question are for approval of the Act, Section 1 of this Act shall become of full force and
40 effect on January 1, 2027. If the Act is not so approved or if the election is not conducted
41 as provided in this section, Section 1 of this Act shall not become effective, and this Act shall
